		{
			dependencies: ["104E7094B28E8114"]
			description: [
				"Your first way to manipulate fluids is by using the create components."
				""
				"&e-&r They are made using bronze, and since you probably don't have a smeltery yet, you can make &9Bronze Blends&r in a pestle and mortar and then heat them."
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&9Mechanical Pump&r: is a mechanical component that pumps fluids when energized. You can energize it using cogwheels."
				""
				"&e-&r it is possible to change whether it will pull or push fluids according to the direction of rotation"
				""
				"By pressing &9W&r and hovering over &5Mechanical Pump&r, you can see the weight of the structure."
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&9Fluid Pipe&r: used as a path through which fluids will flow"
				""
				"&e-&r You can click with the wrench to show which fluid is flowing through the pipe"
				"&e-&r Using &9Copper Casings&r you can lock a connection, thus avoiding logistical errors in nearby pipes"
				""
				"By pressing &9W&r and hovering over &5Fluid Pipe&r, you can see the weight of the structure."
				""
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&9Fluid Tanks&r: are used to store fluids"
				""
				"&e-&r Have 8 storage buckets"
				"&e-&r Can form multiblocks (2x2, 3x3)"
				""
				"By pressing &9W&r and hovering over &5Fluid Tank&r, you can see the weight of the structure."
			]
			icon: "create:fluid_tank"
			id: "0943528D87916444"
			shape: "circle"
			subtitle: "&5Craft fluid related items"
			tasks: [
